> Andrew Burke Cole "Andy"  
Tekonsha Passed Away: 06/27/05  
Publication Date: 06/29/05  
  
  
Andrew Burke "Andy" Cole, age 19, of Tekonsha, died at Bronson Hospital in Kalamazoo on Monday, June 27, 2005. 

Andy died as the result of injuries sustained in an automobile accident on Friday, June 24 near Tekonsha.  
  
Andy was born June 26, 1986 in Marshall to Allen Burke Cole and Becky (Clute) Cole. He has lived in Tekonsha all of his life.  
  
He graduated from Tekonsha High School in June of 2004. While in High School, he was a member of the basketball, football and baseball teams. As a freshman, he received the Steve Weller Award. He was recognized as a Scholar Athlete and the Tekonsha High School basketball team?s Most Valuable Defensive Player. 

Andy was awarded the Michigan Competitive Scholarship and Ritchie Yates Super Athlete Award. He was an honor student, and was a member of the Tekonsha High School Snowcoming Court his freshman year, and their Homecoming Court both his Junior and Senior years. He received the Tekonsha Firefighters Scholarship at graduation also. 

Andy attended the Tech Center in Battle Creek his sophomore and junior years, studying in their Law Enforcement program. He was a member of the National Honor Society there.  
  
Currently, he was a student at Kellogg Community College?s Law Enforcement program, and worked at the Marshall K-Mart Store in the Lawn and Garden department. He was to become a member of the Tekonsha Fire Department at their June 27 meeting.  
  
Andy loved hunting and fishing with his father since he was a small boy. His favorite sport of all was basketball. By his parents honoring Andy?s own wishes, he became a Gift Of Life donor after his death. He will still be helping other?s for many years to come.  
  
Surviving are his mother, Becky Nystrom and father, Allen Burke Cole , his sisters, Stephanie Cole and Andrea Cole, and brothers, Burke Cole and Eric Lewallen all of Tekonsha; maternal grandparents Helen Wright of Marshall and Roger and Marge Clute of Jackson; paternal grandparents, Burke and Tina Cole of Tekonsha and Ellen and Gary Miller of Burlington; his special girlfriend, Sara Cummins of Tekonsha; his special family, Les and Vicki Erickson and Monica Davis all of Marshall, Scott Nystrom of Albion, and Daryl, Vicki and Nick Cummins of Tekonsha; aunts, uncles and cousins.  
  
He was preceded in death by maternal grandfather Gene Wright in 1993.  
  
Friends may call at Craig K. Kempf Funeral Home in Marshall on Thursday from 9:00 a.m. to 9:00 p.m., where family will be present to gather with friends and share memories from 2:00 to 4:00 and 6:00 to 8:00 p.m.  
  
Services to remember and celebrate his life will be held at the Tekonsha High School Gym on Friday at 10:00 a.m.  
  
Interment will follow in Riverside Cemetery in Tekonsha.  
  
Memorials may be made to Tekonsha Firefighters Scholarship Fund.  
  
Assistance with memorials is available at Kempf Funeral Home.
